docs.abstract: Reid, who has criticized Jenkins for ceasing to protest after striking a deal with the N.F.L., exchanged words with Jenkins before the game and criticized him afterward.
docs.snippet: Reid, who has criticized Jenkins for ceasing to protest after striking a deal with the N.F.L., exchanged words with Jenkins before the game and criticized him afterward.
docs.lead_paragraph: Eric Reid, the Carolina Panthers safety known for protesting during the national anthem, has long been open about the contempt he holds for Philadelphia Eagles defensive back Malcolm Jenkins. That animosity spilled over into an on-field confrontation Sunday before the teams had even played a down.

headline.main: Eric Reid Calls Malcolm Jenkins ‘Sellout’ After Confrontation

docs.abstract: The ideological bent of those overseeing collegiate life is having the biggest impact on campus culture.
docs.snippet: The ideological bent of those overseeing collegiate life is having the biggest impact on campus culture.
docs.lead_paragraph: I received a disconcerting email this year from a senior staff member in the Office of Diversity and Campus Engagement at Sarah Lawrence College, where I teach. The email was soliciting ideas from the Sarah Lawrence community for a conference, open to all of us, titled “Our Liberation Summit.” The conference would touch on such progressive topics as liberation spaces on campus, Black Lives Matter and justice for women as well as for lesbian, gay, bisexual, transgender, queer, intersex, asexual and allied people.

headline.main: Think Professors Are Liberal? Try School Administrators

docs.abstract: An officer’s shooting of a teenager shocked the city. His conviction should force the city to act.
docs.snippet: An officer’s shooting of a teenager shocked the city. His conviction should force the city to act.
docs.lead_paragraph: Chicago erupted three years ago when the city belatedly released a video showing that a white officer had essentially executed a black teenager named Laquan McDonald and that the police and city officials lied about it for months. The public’s outrage drove the police superintendent and county prosecutor from their jobs. Last Friday, 12 jurors convicted the officer, Jason Van Dyke, of second-degree murder after less than eight hours of deliberation.

headline.main: Can a Murder Verdict Help Reform Chicago Police?
headline.print_headline: It’s Past Time to Fix the Chicago Police
